Detailed Description

This header defines the GTI APIs to determine the capabilities of the driver and to control the configuration and parameters of the driver.

Copyright (c) 1998-2019, Texas Instruments Inc., All rights reserved.

Function Documentation

GTI_EXPORT GTI_RETURN_TYPE GTI_CONFIG ( GTI_HANDLE_TYPE  hpid,
GTI_CONFIGPARAM_TYPE **  ppParamList,
GTI_STRING_TYPE  szBoardName,
enum CONFIG_FUNCTION_TYPE  flag 
)

GTI_CONFIG() - Controls getting and setting configuration parameters.

This call allows discovery of what configuration parameters the driver supports, and then lets the caller choose what configurations to set. This should only be called after GTI_INIT_EX() and before GTI_CONNECT().

In legacy mode, a setup application would use the discovery mode to determine what parameters could be set. Currently, this is not required because the parameters are now described in the driver's XML files, and this API may be used only to set the parameters.

ppParamList is used to retrieve or send the configuration structure.
szBoardName is the debug probe and target name (minus the '/' cpu name) as was used for pathName in the GTI_INIT_EX() call.

Set flag to CONFIG_GET to retrieve the available parameters. The parameters will be returned via ppParamList as a GTI_CONFIGPARAM_TYPE struct.
Set flag to CONFIG_SET to set specific configurations. Pass the requested parameters via ppParamList as a GTI_CONFIGPARAM_TYPE struct.
Set flag to CONFIG_END to tell the driver to free any memory used during the configuration process.

Returns:
0 on success, -1 on error.
Parameters:
[in]hpidGTI API instance handle.
[in,out]ppParamListPointer to configuration struct.
[in]szBoardNameDebug probe and target name.
[in]flagFlag to determine function type.
GTI_EXPORT GTI_CAP_TYPE GTI_GET_EXT_CAPABILITIES ( GTI_HANDLE_TYPE  hpid,
GTI_INT_TYPE  id 
)

GTI_GET_EXT_CAPABILITIES() - Gets the supported features of the driver.

Returns a collection of capability flags detailing what features the driver supports. Lets you select which set of capability flags are returned: basic features, emulation features, or simulation features.

Set id to GTI_GEN_CAP for basic capabilities (GTI_CAPABLE_ flags).
Set id to GTI_EMU_CAP for emulation capabilities (GTI_EMUCAP_ flags).
Set id to GTI_SIM_CAP for simulation capabilities (GTI_SIMCAP_ flags).

Returns:
the feature/capability flags for requested capability type.
Parameters:
[in]hpidGTI API instance handle.
[in]idWhich type of capablities to return.
GTI_EXPORT GTI_CAP_TYPE GTI_GET_NON_INTRUSIVE_CAPABILITIES ( GTI_HANDLE_TYPE  hpid )

GTI_GET_NON_INTRUSIVE_CAPABILITIES() - Gets the non-intrusive features of the driver.

If exported by the driver, this call returns a collection of flags that define what non-intrusive features the driver supports (GTI_REALTIME_CABABLE_ flags). A return of 0 indicates the driver has no support for non-instrusive features; all accesses to memory, registers, and breakpoints must be done while the target is halted. Otherwise, the flags for the supported features are set in the return value. If the driver supports full realtime mode (GTI_CAPABLE_REAL_TIME), this call is ignored, and all non-intrusive accesses are assumed to be available. Make this call only after GTI_CONNECT().

Returns:
the non-intrusive capability flags for the driver.
Parameters:
[in]hpidGTI API instance handle.
GTI_EXPORT GTI_PROCID_TYPE GTI_GET_PROC_ID ( GTI_HANDLE_TYPE  hpid )

GTI_GET_PROC_ID() - Get Proc ID of target device.

Returns a 32-bit identifier, the Proc ID, of the target device. Note that the GTI API instance handle (hpid) is optional, and you may call this before calling GTI_INIT_EX() by passing in 0 for hpid. If you do so, then this call returns a generic Proc ID for the device type(s) the driver supports. If called with a valid hpid after calling GTI_CONNECT(), the driver may return a more specific Proc ID for the connected device.

GTI_EXPORT GTI_PROCID_TYPE GTI_GET_PROC_MINOR_ID ( GTI_HANDLE_TYPE  hpid )

GTI_GET_PROC_MINOR_ID() - Get minor revision of target device.

Returns a 32-bit minor revision number used to differentiate between versions of devices that share the same Proc ID. This should only be called after GTI_CONNECT() because this call may need to read information from the target to determine the revision.

Returns:
device minor revision.
Parameters:
[in]hpidGTI API instance handle.
GTI_EXPORT GTI_RETURN_TYPE GTI_GETPROCTYPE ( GTI_HANDLE_TYPE  hpid )

GTI_GETPROCTYPE() - Get device type of device driver.

Returns the device type supported by the driver as defined in the GTI_PROCESSOR_TYPE enum. Note that the GTI API instance handle (hpid) is not used, so this can be called before calling GTI_INIT_EX().

While this call is fully supported, it is preferred to use the GTI_GET_PROC_ID() call instead to determine what type of target is being accessed.

Returns:
device type.
Parameters:
[in]hpidGTI API instance handle (unused).
GTI_EXPORT GTI_RETURN_TYPE GTI_GETREV ( GTI_HANDLE_TYPE  hpid )

GTI_GETREV() - Retrieve the GTI API revision of driver.

Returns the revision of the GTI API that was used to build the driver. This is used to ensure the API headers match the API used in the driver; this value should match the GTI_REV definition in gti.h.

Returns:
revision of the GTI API in the driver.
Parameters:
[in]hpidGTI API instance handle.
GTI_EXPORT GTI_RETURN_TYPE GTI_QUERY_INTERFACE ( GTI_HANDLE_TYPE  hpid,
GTI_STRING_TYPE  feature_name,
GTI_UINT32_TYPE  version,
GTI_HANDLE_TYPE *  feature_handle,
GTI_UINT32_TYPE *  supported_version,
GTI_QUERY_INTF_ERROR_TYPE *  error,
GTI_HANDLE_TYPE *  obj_inst 
)

GTI_QUERY_INTERFACE() - Query for additional GTI features.

A generic interface to query for custom GTI features. The purpose of adding such a generic query interface is to avoid adding new GTI API when a new feature (function) is added - such as the function of read cache TAG data.

Returns:
0 on success, -1 on error. Explanation of error is returned via the error parameter.
Parameters:
[in]hpidGTI API instance handle.
[in]feature_nameRequested feature name.
[in]versionRequested feature version.
[out]feature_handleFunction pointer to the feature.
[out]supported_versionFeature version supported.
[out]errorReason for error return.
[out]obj_instObject instance to use with feature.
GTI_EXPORT GTI_RETURN_TYPE GTI_SETUP_PROPERTIES ( GTI_STRING_TYPE  board_cpuName,
GTI_STRING_TYPE *  names,
GTI_STRING_TYPE *  values,
GTI_LEN_TYPE  nProperties 
)

GTI_SETUP_PROPERTIES() - Sets the configuration parameters of the driver.

Call this immediately before GTI_INIT_EX() to set the driver's configuration parameters. Parameters are passed as a pair of arrays. names contains the text names of the parameters, and values contains the values as strings. board_cpuName is the debug probe name and target name (minus the '/' cpu name) as was used for pathName in the GTI_INIT_EX() call.

If the driver does not export this call, then it may use GTI_CONFIG() to set its configuration parameters.

Returns:
0 on success, -1 on error.
Parameters:
[in]board_cpuNameDebug probe and target name.
[in]namesArray of strings containing the configuration parameter names.
[in]valuesArray of strings containing the parameter values.
[in]nPropertiesThe number of parameters in the names and values arrays.
